Steps for frontend deployment

First ask developer the repo name (as of now the code is in gitlab and it can be store anywhere gitlab, github etc)

Then clone repo in your local system  (make one directory similar to your repo name as of now my repo name is explorer-native-frontend)

Then ask env’s from developer, once you get the env 

Then make one directory with name .env where you have clone the repo (sudo nano .env .production and paste your env’s there)

Then navigate to aws dashboard

Then navigate to ecr repo

Then click on you repo 

Then click on view docker command 

Then execute all the docker command where you have cloned the repo 

Once image is pushed in your ecr repo 

Then modify your deployment and service file copy your ecr repo url and paste in the place of image

Similarly modify your service file (change port num, namespace) and execute the file
